cs.DS, cs.NE, cs.DC, cs.SI, cs.AL. 

The paper deals with hopsets, which are a fundamental graph-theoretic and graph-algorithmic construct used for distance-related problems. This makes cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) the most likely category. The paper also discusses distributed routing, which suggests that it could belong to cs.NE (Networks and Internet Architecture) or cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The use of hopsets for distance-related problems also suggests cs.AL (Computational Geometry) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as possible categories.
